# PLAN — Omni Editing Model (the "edit intel" lane)

Third lane, sits on top of the two we shipped:
`footage intel` (perceive the pixels) → **`edit intel` (decide the cut)** →
render substrate (wavelet / HyperFrames) executes it. Sibling to
[[docs/PLAN.footage-intel]] and [[docs/PLAN.content-intelligence]].

Source brief: `~/Downloads/Omni Video Editing Model Architecture Roadmap.md`
(Shane, 2026-07-08), reconciled against the real Reactable stack + the business
constraint, then hardened with **three parallel mid-2026 research passes**
(training/RL/data-infra · base-VLM/architecture · CoreML/ANE/16 GB) on
2026-07-08. Approved end-to-end plan mirror: `~/.claude/plans/vast-strolling-sunset.md`.

**Thesis (settled over discussion):** we are training a **world model of the
TIMELINE, not the frame.** State = an editable scene-graph / HyperFrames
timeline (a text-serializable IR). Dynamics = our deterministic renderer
(exact, ~300 ms — we never *learn* to simulate). Value = taste. The task is
structurally a **GUI / code-action agent**: perceive a structured scene → emit
typed actions. Our unfair advantages: a **free, exact verifier** (renderer +
fidelity gate) and a **data flywheel** nobody else has.

---

## 0. Reframe — two things the research brief gets wrong for us

**(a) It is framed "Mac-native, locally-runnable"; our business is metered.**
Shane's ruling: *"charge API tokens for it, and it's not a local model."* So
the revenue path is **Qwen3-VL-8B hosted on Modal**, billed through the existing
credit gateway (`/api/gateway/chat` → CreditLedger DO). **Resolution (research):**
we *also* ship a **local Apple-Silicon tier** — a distilled 2–3B model on the
**ANE (CoreML)** — but as a strategic fast-follow (offline, no per-token cost,
frees the GPU), not the primary. Same base family both tiers. Local perception
(ANE Depth-Anything, Gemma/SmolVLM) stays free.

**(b) ~60% of the brief's "phased build plan" is already shipped.** We have the
perception + rendering layers, better-fit (deterministic, license-clean, on-metal):

| Brief's proposed layer | What we already ship |
|---|---|
| L1 Perception — Depth Pro + Video-Depth-Anything | **native ANE** Depth-Anything-V2-Small ([[native/vision]], 48 MB, ~12% CPU) + Modal DA2 fallback |
| L1 Segmentation/tracking — DINOv3 + Florence-2 | **SAM 3.1** concept tracking on Modal ([[gpu/modal_footage.py]]) → `tracks.jsonl` COCO-RLE |
| L1 semantic features | **SigLIP-2** embeddings + **SmolVLM-500M** captions ([[scripts/footage-embed.py]]) |
| OCR / transcript | Apple Vision OCR ([[scripts/ocr-frames.swift]]) + Moonshine/whisper word-ts |
| L4 Structured output — "teach a VLM HyperFrames HTML" | **wavelet render-core** (native Rust, byte-deterministic, 297 ms/72×1080p30) + **wavelet-ui** (135 Remocn comps) + HyperFrames |
| L3 Synthesis — diffusion | *parked* — §4/§9-P8, compose-only edits never need it |
| the edit itself | **`video autoedit` + `video compose`** already emit edits — from GROUND TRUTH, no model |

The brief's Phase 1 (perception) + Phase 3 (renderer integration) are **done**.
What's missing = the two parts Shane named: **harness intelligence** and
**editing-substrate intelligence** — plus the moat the brief never mentions:
**the data flywheel**.

---

## 1. The three-part system, mapped to real components

```
        ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
        │  (A) DIRECTOR   — taste, narrative, ambiguity │  MiniMax via
        │      metered, smartest, we already have it    │  /api/gateway/chat
        └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────┘  (KEEP; reduce reliance)
                                 │ delegates well-scoped edit tasks
        ┌───────────────────────▼─────────────────────┐
        │  (B) HARNESS    — memory, attention, routing  │  Reactable agent loop
        │      loop-based test-time compute; AutoPoet   │  + Nexus (memory/attn)
        │      self-learning; picks director vs editor  │  ← WE DON'T HAVE YET
        └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────┘
                                 │ (perception in, actions out)
        ┌───────────────────────▼─────────────────────┐
        │  (C) EDITOR     — footage-intel + intent      │  Qwen3-VL LoRA on
        │      → structured edit actions in OUR DSL     │  Modal (+ local ANE)
        │      cheap, narrow, deeply fluent in us       │  ← WE DON'T HAVE YET
        └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────┘
                                 │ edit spec (video verbs / wavelet comp)
        ┌───────────────────────▼─────────────────────┐
        │  SUBSTRATE — footage intel (perceive) +       │  ALREADY SHIPPED
        │  wavelet/HyperFrames (render, deterministic)  │
        └───────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **(A) Director = MiniMax gateway.** Taste, story arc, ambiguous intent,
  whole-project understanding. Stays. Goal is *reduce reliance / cut cost*.
- **(B) Harness = agent loop + Nexus.** Where "loop-based thinking" + AutoPoet
  self-learning live. Orchestration, not a model: routes director↔editor,
  retrieves similar past edits as attention/context, runs the
  propose→render→observe→revise loop (§4, §8 cascade).
- **(C) Editor = the model we train.** The "editing-substrate intelligence" a la
  Gemini Omni — but narrow, fluent-in-us. Qwen3-VL, metered on Modal.

---

## 2. The editor model, precisely (the thing we train)

**It does not need to be smart, general, or pixel-generative — it needs to be
fluent in us.** Two constraints collapse the problem:

1. **Pixels are already digested.** The `footage-intel/1` sidecar
   ([[docs/PLAN.footage-intel]]) turns a clip into structured tokens: shots,
   transcript w/ word-ts, OCR, tracklets w/ boxes + depth zones, SigLIP
   embeddings, captions, `events.jsonl` ground truth. The editor reads the
   **sidecar**, not raw frames (frames only when it must).
2. **The action space is bounded + deterministic.** Output is a **structured
   edit spec in our own DSL**: `video` verbs (`autoedit`/`compose`/`matte`/
   `motion`), a wavelet comp, wavelet-ui component instances (135 typed comps).
   The renderer executes it byte-deterministically; the gate grades it.

So the editor's job is a **narrow structured translation**:
`(footage-intel sidecar + project context + intent) → a valid, renderable edit
spec in OUR action space.`

Design commitments:
- **Coordinates, not adjectives** — emit normalized points/boxes on the stage
  rect (the `autoedit.ts::makeMapper` convention), as **discrete location
  tokens** on a fixed grid, not free floats. The DeepSeek-OCR / Gemini-Omni
  spatial-grounding property; trainable + checkable.
- **Base = Qwen3-VL** (§5). LoRA. 8B on Modal, distilled 2–3B on the ANE tier.
- **Never emit pixels (or prose) when a deterministic composite + coordinate
  spec suffices.** Generative synthesis is a separate, gated, later lane (§9-P8).

---

## 3. The data flywheel — the moat the brief misses (full strategy in §6)

We manufacture training data the way almost nobody can, owning a **deterministic
edit substrate + a ground-truth authored corpus + an automatic grader**:

- **`video autoedit` is a free labeling function.** Every authored take gives
  `(ground-truth events → correct edit plan)` with zero inference — the
  presenter's cursor/click/slide/layout events *are* the label. Reverse-generate
  an instruction and you have a verified `(sidecar, instruction, edit-spec)` triple.
- **The fidelity gate + eval = the reward model.** `just wavelet-gate` (SSIM +
  byte-determinism) + `scripts/eval` checkers grade a render against ground-truth
  state — a ready reward signal for BoN/RL and a hard data filter.
- **wavelet-ui (135 comps) + video verbs = a typed, closed action space** —
  synthetic data can be generated *and* validated against the schema.

This is where **"our opinions"** become weights: our punch-in timing, silence-trim
policy, component vocabulary, coordinate convention. The flywheel is the spine;
the model is downstream of it.

---

## 4. Research threads, placed (assigned a job)

- **DeepSeek-OCR (optical context compression + point grounding)** → (i) encode
  keyframes/sidecar as few optical tokens so long footage fits the window;
  (ii) train coordinate output (§2).
- **Loop-based thinking / test-time compute** → the harness runs
  **propose → render preview → footage-intel on the model's OWN output → compare
  → revise.** The 300 ms renderer is the verifier; lives in the harness, not the
  weights (realized as the §8 cascade).
- **DSpark (RESOLVED — it's DeepSeek's speculative-decoding serving stack,
  V4-Flash/Pro; 60–85% faster, distribution-preserving; semi-AR block drafting +
  confidence-scheduled verification).** Placement: **token-level spec-dec within
  our OWN self-hosted family** (editor-small drafts for editor-large) → cheaper
  Modal serving. **NOT against MiniMax** (different tokenizer + API-only, no
  logits). Shane's "is our model the draft model?" → yes at the **artifact level**
  (the §8 cascade: editor drafts an edit, renderer verifies), and optionally at
  the token level within our family. Research spike: semi-AR *block* drafting maps
  unusually well to our structured DSL (independent components draft in parallel).
- **AutoPoet self-learning** → harness curates its own corpus; every gate-verified
  episode appends to the training log; periodic LoRA refresh (§9-P7). Nexus =
  long-term episodic/style memory served as retrieval.
- **MiniMax M3** → philosophy only (native multimodal, sparse long-context). Not a
  base (428B, MSA unsupported by serving stacks).
- **V-JEPA 2 (Meta)** → confirms the thesis (latent, predict-representations-not-
  pixels) but not a core role: its world-model capability is *physical* dynamics /
  robot planning — the thing we deleted (renderer = exact dynamics; recorded
  footage already has the future). Slot only as a **candidate temporal-embedding
  producer in footage-intel** (swappable behind the sidecar contract, like
  EdgeTAM), evaluated vs SigLIP-2 on retrieval; ~1B, likely a cloud pass. NOT the
  editor backbone (it's an encoder, not a VLM — Qwen3-VL covers that).
- **BAGEL-7B / Omni-Video-2 (diffusion synthesis)** → deferred generative lane
  (§9-P8); only for edits needing *new* pixels. Compose-only edits never invoke it.

---

## 5. Architecture decisions (mid-2026 research → chosen)

- **Base = Qwen3-VL, two tiers, same family.** 8B-Instruct (Apache-2.0) on the
  Modal API tier; 4B → distilled **2–3B** on the local ANE tier. Why: best spatial
  grounding + native video + timestamp tokens (matches our word-timed transcript);
  **DeepStack** multi-level feature injection = the graft point for depth/SigLIP;
  first-class `mlx-vlm` support. Backups: **Molmo 2** (native normalized pointing +
  video tracking), **InternVL3.5-8B** (clean license, OCR/UI-heavy), **Apple
  FastVLM** (ships MLX *and* CoreML — the on-device engine / distillation target).
- **A/B a code-LLM baseline.** Input is already text, output is code (DSL); SFT
  **Qwen2.5-Coder-7B over the serialized graph** and A/B vs the VLM. VLM earns its
  keep mainly at coordinate grounding. Decide empirically at §9-P3/P4.
- **Task framing = GUI/code-action agent.** Mirror **UI-TARS 3-stage**
  (grounding → CoT SFT → RL-in-sandbox) + **Aguvis** (thoughts-before-action) +
  **OS-Atlas** (freeze the ~135 verbs as a closed unified action space) +
  **CodeAct** (emit code actions, not flat JSON). **Our renderer is the RL sandbox.**
- **Conditioning (feed the sidecar):** (A) serialize the symbolic scene graph
  (shots/boxes/depth-zones/transcript/OCR/captions) as **structured text** — first,
  cheap; (B) inject dense features via **depth-as-per-patch positional encoding**
  (SD-VLM, ~0 extra tokens) + SigLIP/DINO through an **MLP or DeepStack-level**
  projector, with **zero-init gates** so pretrained weights aren't destabilized.
  Sample frames **at our shot boundaries**; add timestamp tokens; EVS/3D-resampler
  compression for long clips.
- **Output validity:** coordinates = **discrete location tokens** (fixed grid).
  Enforce the DSL with **xgrammar** — **only on the final DSL block** (constraining
  the whole output degrades reasoning 10–30%; reason free-form first, then switch
  the grammar on — CRANE). Grammar buys syntax, not semantics (in-range coords /
  valid IDs / temporal order come from training + the verifier).

---

## 6. Data strategy (folds in the Scrape-Creators discussion)

**Two engines, inverses, both mint `(video ↔ timeline)` pairs:**
- **Engine A — Synthesis (forward, EXACT):** procedurally author valid timelines
  from wavelet-ui (135 comps) + verbs → render → pairs with *zero label noise*,
  unlimited, 100%-owned. Teaches the IR + grounding.
- **Engine B — Decompiler-skeletonize (reverse, APPROXIMATE):** real video →
  sidecar → abstract edit skeleton. **Keep structure** (cut timing, layer types,
  transitions, motion curves, normalized coords), **STRIP content** (footage,
  verbatim brand text, logos). Teaches realism.

**Sources & policy:** synthetic + own recorded takes = unrestricted, start here.
**Scrape Creators** = procurement across organic/paid/YouTube/Shorts (cleaner than
self-scraping — moves platform download-ToS to SC). **Ads are the best realism
domain** but train on the *skeleton*, never the ad. Checks before found-content
training: **SC ToS on ML-training/redistribution** + **IP-counsel sign-off**
(§11). Default-safe path needing no sign-off: synthetic + own takes.

**Discipline (research-mandated):** **accumulate, never replace** — real takes +
skeletons stay in every training mix as an anchor (prevents model collapse); track
real:synthetic ratio. **Diversity-controlled** generation (cover all 135 comps +
edge cases). **Curriculum:** single verb → single-component overlay →
multi-component composition → full timeline. Mine real NL intents from takes so
*prompts* aren't synthetic even when timelines are. Quantize coords to the grid.
**Scale:** 2–5k clean examples ≈ 80% of value; 10–50k for full coverage.

---

## 7. Training recipe (assembled from research)

1. **SFT (behavior cloning).** Unsloth on Modal; **QLoRA (4-bit NF4) + DoRA**,
   r=16–32, α=2r, target `all-linear` in the decoder, **vision tower + merger
   frozen** (perception pre-serialized), LoRA+ on, **PiSSA init** (fewer steps →
   spot-preemption-friendly), lr~1e-4, 2–3 epochs. Loss on DSL tokens; keep a
   free-form reasoning prefix.
2. **Best-of-N self-distillation (the main "RL").** Sample N per prompt →
   render+SSIM+checker score (free) → SFT on winners → iterate 2–3 rounds. Beats
   online RL per-unit-compute, stable, reuses SFT infra; our free exact reward
   removes its only downside.
3. **Online RLVR (GRPO/GSPO) — only if BoN plateaus / persistent failure modes.**
   Hierarchical gated reward: **validity gate (grammar+checker) → SSIM fidelity →
   parsimony**; KL to SFT ref. Adds the negative gradient BoN lacks; gating is the
   proven anti-reward-hacking structure.
4. **Taste (thin, late).** **KTO** on binary app telemetry (kept/discarded, thumbs
   — no pairs needed); DPO/SimPO if we curate ranked pairs. Verifier scores
   correctness; KTO scores aesthetics.
5. **(Later) On-policy distillation** once a director/frontier-authored corpus
   exists (matches RL quality at ~10–30× less compute).

**Tooling:** Unsloth primary (single-GPU VLM GRPO), ms-swift fallback. Training is
CUDA/Modal; `mlx-vlm` QLoRA on the M4 only for 2–4B prototyping + pipeline debug
(app closed) — **not** real runs. **Modal cost:** L40S/A100-40 SFT ≈ **$5–30/run**;
optional light RLVR pass ≈ **$50–300**; spot + Volume adapter checkpoints + PiSSA.

---

## 8. Serving & deployment (two tiers + the draft/cascade)

- **Modal API tier (revenue):** Qwen3-VL-8B, metered through the credit gateway.
  **xgrammar** on the final block + **serve-time best-of-k reranked by our own
  renderer** (near-free quality). **DSpark-style speculative decoding within our
  own family** — editor-small drafts for editor-large, both self-hosted → 60–85%
  faster serving.
- **Local ANE tier (Mac-native, strategic):** distilled **2–3B, 4-bit palettized
  (per-grouped-channel), stateful `MLState` KV cache, Conv2d-1×1 attention,
  fixed-shape buckets, chunked >1 GB**; FastViT-HD-style encoder → few visual
  tokens. **Vision encoder → ANE always** (like Depth-Anything). Rationale: the app
  saturates the GPU with capture + wavelet render, so ANE **frees the GPU and runs
  cool** (~2–13 W vs 20–25 W); our workload is near best-case for ANE (**prefill-
  heavy, short DSL output**). MLX-GPU fallback for long outputs when the GPU is free.
- **The cascade (three-part system, realized):** **editor drafts an edit → renderer
  verifies (free, exact) → MiniMax director only on taste/ambiguity (rare).**
  Draft-and-verify at the *artifact* level (works with an API director — we
  exchange whole edits, not logits). This is where "cut reliance on MiniMax" happens.

---

## 9. Phased build — each ships value AND de-risks the next

Ordering principle: **collect the data you're already generating before training
anything.** P0–P2 need **no training and no GPU** — useful regardless, and the
prerequisites the world model hangs on. P3 is the go/no-go before a dollar of GPU.

- **P0 — Flywheel capture + verifier-as-reward.** Log every edit as
  `(sidecar, intent, edit-spec, render, gate/checker score)` into an `edit-intel/`
  corpus; wrap gate/checker as a reusable reward fn. Hook `autoedit`, `compose`,
  agent-authored edits. *De-risks:* the tuple + grader. No training.
- **P1 — Skeletonizing decompiler (encoder + Engine B).** `video → abstract edit
  skeleton` (structure kept, content stripped). *De-risks:* the world-model
  abstraction; it's the data factory.
- **P2 — Synthetic-pair generator (Engine A).** Procedural author → render → exact
  pairs, diversity-controlled + curriculum-ordered. *De-risks:* IR coverage.
- **P3 — Frozen-base baseline, NO training (GO/NO-GO).** Sidecar + action schema +
  Nexus-retrieved similar edits in-context to MiniMax/Qwen3-VL + best-of-k via
  renderer; coder-LLM A/B. Measure on authored *and* imported clips. *De-risks:* is
  the sidecar enough context? where does frozen fail (= the training set)?
- **P4 — SFT v1 on Modal (editor v1, metered).** QLoRA+DoRA on the corpus; deploy
  8B behind the gateway. *Ships:* cheaper edits + measured MiniMax-reliance drop.
- **P5 — Best-of-N self-distillation.** *Ships:* quality jump, no bigger model.
- **P6 — Local ANE tier.** Distill → 2–3B → CoreML (palettize/stateful/chunk) →
  ship on-device, GPU-free.
- **P7 — Taste RL + self-learning.** KTO on telemetry; periodic LoRA refresh from
  gate-verified episodes; Nexus as long-term style memory.
- **P8 (optional) — spec-dec serving (small drafts large) + synthesis lane**
  (BAGEL/Omni-Video-2 for new-pixel edits, gated behind compose-can't-do-it).

---

## 10. What NOT to do

- **Don't** train a general VLM from scratch — M3's lesson; value = narrowness +
  fluency in our own substrate.
- **Don't** predict pixels — predict *state* (timeline). The instant you generate
  frames you've rebuilt Sora badly.
- **Don't** host the metered model on the laptop — the metered brain is Modal; the
  laptop runs free perception + the distilled ANE tier.
- **Don't** let the model emit pixels/prose when a deterministic composite +
  coordinate spec does the job.
- **Don't** invent a new edit language — `video` verbs + wavelet-ui + the
  footage-intel sidecar **are** the I/O contract.
- **Don't** constrain the whole decode with the grammar (reasoning tax); final
  block only.
- **Don't** put phases in front of the flywheel — no training before P0–P2 give a
  corpus + grader.
- **Don't** scale synthetic data infinitely — accumulate-with-real-anchor beats volume.

