## 12. Build log

- **2026-07-08 — P0/P1/P2-v0/P3 + tracklet-merge + P4-pipeline shipped + verified** (reactable repo, `main`, working tree, uncommitted).
  - **P0 flywheel** — `cli/lib/edit-intel.ts` + capture hooks in `video autoedit`/`compose` + `edit-intel stats`. Every edit → an `edit-intel/episodes.jsonl` tuple (edit-spec stored out-of-line, render fingerprint, `gold`/`model` score with a `gate` slot for P3+). Best-effort; `REACTABLE_EDIT_INTEL=0` disables. Verified on the fixture + a real take (2 punch-ins / 65.7 s trimmed, render sha captured).
  - **P1 decompiler (Engine B / encoder)** — `cli/lib/decompile.ts` + `video decompile <ref> [--verify]` → `edit-skeleton/1` IR: timeline segments (kind + transition) · text regions (role + normalized bbox + text_shape, string STRIPPED) · subject layers (generic class + depth zone + keyframed motion) · speech/silence timing (word counts, no words). **Strip contract proven** — `--verify` leak check green, source OCR strings absent from output; take (`kind:take`) and imported (`kind:imported`, filename stripped) both work. Producer-agnostic — reads `tracks.jsonl`, so EdgeTAM/SAM/any tracker flows through unchanged.
  - **P2-v0 synthetic (Engine A)** — `cli/lib/synth.ts` + `synth pairs [--n --seed]`: deterministic ffmpeg clips (dark/light alternating shots) → round-trip (index → decompile → compare vs authored) → **5/5 segment-count match, 9 ms mean boundary MAE** (< 1 frame @30fps). Mints `(sidecar ↔ authored skeleton)` pairs into the corpus.
  - **P3 frozen-base go/no-go** — `cli/lib/baseline.ts` + `baseline <ref> [--k]`: serialize the sidecar scene-graph → frozen **MiniMax-M3** emits `edit-skeleton/1` (best-of-k) → scored vs the decompiler; best captured as a `model` episode (P0's `model` label now exercised). **VERDICT = GO:** 3/3 valid on synthetic + fixture take, segment-count match, **0 ms boundary MAE**, coords in range/monotonic — and on the take it correctly normalized the OCR bbox, classified role, computed text_shape, and **stripped the literal text**, all with zero training. Confirms the sidecar is sufficient context and the IR is expressible by a frozen model. Caveat: `layer_recall` read 0.03 purely because P1 tracklet-noise inflated ground truth to 67 layers (the model's text layers matched the decompiler) → elevated decompiler tracklet-merge to a training-data prerequisite. **[RESOLVED same day]** `decompile.ts` now merges co-moving tracklets (greedy centroid clustering per concept, `merged_from` provenance kept) — fixture subject layers **65 → 20**, targets clean for P4.
  - **P4 fine-tuning pipeline** — `cli/lib/dataset.ts` + `dataset export` → SFT chat jsonl for the reconstruction task (scene graph → skeleton), reusing the P3 prompt; deterministic train/val split; dedup + "corpus small" guard. `gpu/modal_train.py` — Unsloth QLoRA+DoRA on an L40S, saving a LoRA adapter to a Volume, **estimate-first / `--run`-gated** (no GPU spend without an explicit user-run `modal run`). Dry-validated: 7 unique pairs (5 train/2 val), valid chat rows, script syntax-clean. **The paid training run is user-gated** on (a) a scaled corpus (§7 targets 2–5k) and (b) explicit go. v1 base = a text coder LLM (task is text→text); Qwen3-VL frame path is the follow-up.
  - **Audio understanding (task #6)** — `cli/lib/audio.ts` + `video audio <ref>`: dep-free (ffmpeg PCM → energy envelope) → **kind_segments** (speech/silence/sound), **onsets + tempo estimate** (BPM + confidence — correctly low on speech-only), **speech turns** (`spk0`; true multi-speaker diarization flagged as a model follow-up). Written to the sidecar; the decompiler's `audio` section now emits kind_segments + beats(onset times) + turns + word-count speech_segments — all STRUCTURE (verified: no transcript words leak). Enables cut-on-beat / silence-skip / turn-aware pacing.
  - **Procurement — real content (Engine B) [SC ToS/IP gate cleared by Shane]** — `cli/lib/procure.ts` + `reactable procure "<brand>" [--library fb|tiktok] [--n]` | `--url <u>`. Pulls real ad/creator clips via the Scrape-Creators research proxy (key server-side, session-cookie auth), **downloads ALL pulled creative** (video + image), decompiles videos to **content-stripped skeletons** (leak-checked, refused on any leak) into the corpus, keeps images raw under `edit-intel/procured/` (gitignored). Fixed the SC endpoint (the old `ads()` used a 404 path → now `/v1/facebook/adLibrary/search/ads`, video at `snapshot.videos[0].video_hd_url`); added a 45s download abort (fbcdn stalls hang plain fetch); exposed `research()` from `intel.ts`. **Verified live on "True Classic"**: real FB ad videos → 15-shot content-stripped skeletons; SFT dataset now **11 pairs incl. 3 procured** ad skeletons. Follow-ups: tiktok/instagram video-search shapes; still-frame skeletonizing for image ads; structure-only SFT *input* for procured (content-free both sides).
- **Fix (leak check, all lanes):** the strip-contract check scanned the whole serialized JSON, so common source words false-matched structural tokens (`true` boolean, `text_shape`/`timeline` keys) and wrongly refused real clips. Now scans string VALUES only, words ≥5 chars, minus the skeleton's structural vocabulary. Verified: 4 real ad clips pass, 32–48 content words checked, 0 false positives.
- **Finding (perception):** ffmpeg `scene` scores are content-dependent — a flat-color hard cut measured ~0.13 vs the 0.30 gate (missed); dark/light luma alternation forces reliable synthetic recall. Real-footage scene-detect recall on low-contrast cuts is a footage-intel improvement to track.
- **Follow-ups:** run the P4 paid fine-tune once the corpus is scaled (`synth pairs --n <big>` + real takes; §7 targets 2–5k) + explicit go; Engine A "full" = compose the 135 wavelet-ui components (byte-deterministic) once that lane merges from `reactable-wasmvideo`; text/subject round-trips; true multi-speaker diarization + music/sfx discrimination; Qwen3-VL frame path for the editor; V-JEPA-2 temporal-embedding bake-off vs SigLIP-2.
